  "text": "**Kubernetes/kubernetes**: Health endpoints are implemented via a pluggable `HealthChecker` interface in `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/server/healthz/healthz.go`. The `InstallHandler` (for /healthz), `InstallReadyzHandler` (for /readyz), and `InstallLivezHandler` (for /livez) functions register HTTP handlers. The `healthCheckRegistry` in `healthz.go` (server package) manages per-endpoint check lists. Checks include: `PingHealthz` (always OK), `LogHealthz` (verifies logging isn't blocked), `NewInformerSyncHealthz` (verifies informer caches are synced), `NewShutdownHealthz` (fails when shutdown begins), and etcd health/readiness checks registered in `options/etcd.go` via `addEtcdHealthEndpoint` which calls `storagefactory.CreateHealthCheck` and `CreateReadyCheck`. The `config.go` aggregates HealthzChecks, LivezChecks, and ReadyzChecks. The `genericapiserver.go` ties registries to the server lifecycle.\n\n**Grafana/grafana**: Has three health-related endpoints. (1) `/healthz` in `pkg/api/http_server.go` (`healthzHandler`) \u2014 always returns 200 OK if the HTTP server is running, no dependency checks. (2) `/api/health` in `pkg/api/http_server.go` (`apiHealthHandler`) \u2014 checks database health via `databaseHealthy()` in `pkg/api/health.go`, which runs `SELECT 1` against the DB with a 5-second cache. Returns 503 if DB is unreachable. (3) `/readyz` and `/livez` registered via `pkg/server/health.go` (`RegisterHealthEndpoints`) \u2014 `/livez` always returns 200; `/readyz` uses an atomic `HealthNotifier` boolean. Additionally, `/healthz` and `/readyz` are proxied to the embedded k8s apiserver in `pkg/services/apiserver/service.go`.\n\n**Prometheus/prometheus**: Uses `/-/healthy` and `/-/ready` endpoints (not /healthz, /readyz). Registered in `web/web.go` as simple inline handlers. `/-/healthy` always returns 200 OK with no dependency checks. `/-/ready` is wrapped with `testReady()` which checks an atomic `ReadyStatus` flag with three states: Ready, NotReady, Stopping. The ready status is set in `cmd/prometheus/main.go` \u2014 `SetReady(web.Ready)` is called after config is loaded and TSDB is open; `SetReady(web.Stopping)` on shutdown. No DB/cache/dependency checks are performed \u2014 readiness is purely lifecycle-based.",
